The Deputy Chairman of Lagos State Park Management Committee, Alhaji Sulaiman Ojora (aka Kudety), has assured the Commissioner of Police (CP) Abiodun Alabi that officials of the committee will not involved in any act that will disrupt the peace enjoyed in the state. Ojora said even with the absence of the Park Management Committee Chairman, Alhaji Musiliu Akinsanya (MC Oluomo), who travelled for Umrah (Lesser Hajj), members of the committee have ensured that the officials maintain law and order in discharging their activities.   840,437 pangolins traded illegally     ‘Check underage access to hotels, drugs’     Insecurity: INEC officials to reject election duty   According to him, the committee will continue to support the state government’s efforts to rid the state of criminal activities. He enjoined officials of the committee to go about their lawful duties and avoid provocation from any quarters. Ojora urged security agencies to arrest anyone found involving in any act that breaches the peaceful atmosphere in the state.